investigation.title: Impact of modeled microgravity stress on innate immunity in a beneficial animal-microbe symbiosis
investigation.description: The innate immune response is the first line of defense for all animals to not only detect invading microbes and toxins but also sense and interface with the environment. One such environment that can significantly affect innate immunity is spaceflight.

project.funding: The work was also supported by NASA Space Biology grants 80NSSC19K0138 and 80NSSC18K1465 awarded to JSF and a NASA Florida Space Grant Consortium Dissertation Improvement grant awarded to AAD. The NanoString experiments were supported by public donations made through the crowdfunding site Experiment.com/squidinspace.
